 User Input and Output in C# (Short Description)

User Input: In C#, user input is taken using Console.ReadLine(), which reads input as a string. 
It can be converted to other data types like int, double, etc., using Convert.ToInt32(), Convert.ToDouble(), etc.

Output: Display messages or results using Console.WriteLine() or Console.Write()

Common Data Types:

Type                  Description	                         Example

int	                  Integer numbers	                    int age = 20;
double	              Decimal numbers	                    double price = 99.99;
char	                Single character	                  char grade = 'A';
string	              Text (sequence of chars)	          string name = "Nazifa";
bool	                Boolean (true/false)	              bool isValid = true;
